\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 First of all, could you tell me the date of your birth, and the year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 January, 1899. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname date}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Month}{\xmlattrvalue 1}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Day}{\xmlattrvalue 4}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Year}{\xmlattrvalue 1899}}}January 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \super\insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 , 1899{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Could you tell me approximately how old your parents were when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Mother was 18. Father was about\'85.I wouldn't be sure, Father was about 24, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did you have any brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, I had one sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Born after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, she was 10 years younger than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And so in your early childhood, your first 10 years you were really an only child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did you have many playmates and other children to play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, y
es, you see, we lived in a terrace, a terrace of about 12, no 16 houses and of course, there were children all around and we all played together in the fields, you know, and what one would expect to do in the country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did you play in the street, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 We played \'85
 there were such games as marbles, which we used to play in the gutter, you know, that takes the water, like, by the paths; and then there was Cat and Stick, that's that tipper, you know, you \'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Like tip and run?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes. A piece of 
conduct stick about that length and it's sharpened at each end and so that when you strike the tip it cocks up, you see. We used to play that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Does one person hold the stick, is that the idea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, you used to put what was the 'cat' on the ground
, you see, and it was sharpened at the end, so when you struck it, you see, it tipped up and sort of flew away, you see. We used to play that, and then we used to have hoops, iron hoops which we used to bowl, and we used to run along the street with them.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did girls play that, too?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes, yes. Oh, yes, they played it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did you play any game imitating fox hunting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, we didn't play that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did you have any aunts and uncles and grandparents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes. I don't remember grandparents, but aunts and uncles galore.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 So you had cousins, too, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 One or two, not many cousins.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Can you describe to me what the house was like inside, starting, say, from the ground floor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes. Well, as I said, it was in a terrace and it was a house that \'85
 the terrace was built by the Co-Operative Society, and many of them were purchased by the tenants by leaving the dividend which they get on purchases, they didn't draw it out they left it in the Society and so, after many years, I 
think they were...the houses themselves were built for about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248386 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
120 each and, see, by leaving their dividend in the Society they were eventually able to buy the house, so it was quite a good thing. Mind you, they had to be fortunate, but we were never \'85 my m
other was never able to do that because, sort of losing Father fairly early, you know, she had quite a struggle. So, I mean, that dividend which had accumulated at the end of 6 months she was only too glad to draw out and purchase clothes, shoes, somethin
g like that, you know, that was needed for me. But anyway, I'm digressing, aren't I? You wanted to know about the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, but that was interesting, but I wondered what it was like inside because the interior of a house reflects the way a family liv
es, you know. When you came in, did you come in at the back or the front?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Always the back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 There was a front door?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 There was a front door, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 So you'd come in the back, and what would you walk into?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 We'd walk into the kitchen 
which was a small room which had a cooking range in, but in our particular house the sink and the water tap was in an adjoining room, or building, which we called the wash-house. And in there there was a copper and an open grate fire, and that was where m
other used to do the washing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And did you have any kind of sink in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
No, no, no, we didn't have a sink in the kitchen. Actually, that was removed - the other houses in the row had them in the kitchen, but that was removed by the previo
us tenant, or at least, he had permission to remove it and they added this wash-house on for their convenience, sort of thing. You know, that was like an additional room on our house, you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 How did you get into the wash-house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 You had to go out of the kitchen door and then there was another door in from the garden, or yard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 So you had to go into the open air before you could get to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And so whenever your mother wanted water for cooking, or to rinse a dish, she had to go out there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 She had to go out there, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 In the kitchen what else was there besides the range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, we had a large dresser, you see, with big drawers in, where such things as linen and things like that were kept in, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did she keep anything in the way of crockery, or cooking utensils there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, not in the kitchen, no. Those were kept in a pantry, or cupboard, in the living}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3539421\charrsid6246232  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did she have a table in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, there wasn't room for that, but you see, t
his dressed had a large top, you see, so when she was cooking she had all the things on the top of the dresser, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 That was her work surface?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And any chairs in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes, there was room for a couple of chairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 But it wasn't the kind of kitchen where you ate, and sat about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, no, we never eat in there at all, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 How big was it, then, compared with this room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, about a third of this one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 So it would be about how many feet, do you think? About 10' x 15'?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, it was quite small, and as I say, with this dresser which was two - thirds as big as this table, there was not a lot of room left.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Anything else in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, that completed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did she bake bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, she didn't make bread. We used to buy that from the Co-Operative Society.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did they call round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 They came every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did she do anything in the way of bottling, or preserving, or pickling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, hundreds of lbs. 
You see, we had 3 large greengage trees, so we had...quite a long garden, and we had these 3 large greengage trees which were very prolific, they used to bear regularly, and so she used to bottle dozens of lbs, of that. Then we used to go gathering blackb
erries. There was a wood up here where we used to go and we used to get a lot of those. Plums we used to get. We hadn't any in the garden but we could get \'85
 buy them comparatively cheap, you know, in the neighbourhood. And then we had a couple of apple tree
s. They were no good for preserving but they did help out for all the other things that you use up, and so on. And we had currants, used to bottle them, so that through the season Mother would stock her cupboard right up with, may be 150 lbs. of jam. Chie
fly jam, I don't recall her just preserving fruits, there wasn't a lot of that done then, but jam making, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Where did she store those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, she stored them in the pantry, and then we had another cupboard under the stairs and she used to store s
ome in there. Actually, the house was well provided with cupboards, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And in that room where the pantry was, that was really a cupboard-like room, was it, the pantry? Was it like a sort of larder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, you could walk into it, but it was 
built, again, under the stairs, you see, and the pantry itself was at the extreme end of the room where the stairs had gone up, so you got the height, you see, so you could walk into it and there were shelves all round. It was quite a large pantry for an 
o
rdinary terrace house. And then beside it on the lower portion where the stairs were approaching down there was also this other cupboard, you see, which was about, oh, 4' high, something like that, with a door and you could sort of go in, and she kept thi
n
gs there. And Father always used to keep what was called a 'four and a half' barrel of beer in there. He was an abstemious man, never used public houses, but he always had his cask of beer in, his 'four and a half' what they called it, and he used to draw
 off his glass of beer for his supper.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 That was his drink.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 With his food, or before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, with food, yes, yes. With bread and cheese.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Would he make that beer himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, no, that was purchased from a local brewer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And did he make any wine, or beer at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
Oh, yes, they made no end of wine. Mother used to do that. Oh, wonderful wines. Of course, they made it from vegetables, from parsnip, which was very strong. But her chief sort of wine was her orange wine, and she use
d to buy the oranges from the fruiterer when they were just going off, if they were \'85 you could almost say overripe. And we used to keep, you know, big \'85let me see, now \'85
 I think they were 18 gallon jars, big stone jars, you know that she used to keep it in and it used to ferment in there. That went in the cupboard under the stairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 So she made it with orange and with parsnip?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Sometimes she'd make it with the other fruits, like \'85 you know, sort of blackcurrant, and that sort of thing, but of cour
se they were more expensive to buy and she didn't make much of that. But you see, the overripe \'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 The parsnips were her own, from the garden, were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, they came from the garden, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Do you know how she learnt to make the wines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, I couldn't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 You don't know whether she'd had it handed down from her own mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, you see, this was a great wine-making district. Everybody \'85
 well, when I say everybody you know what I mean, it was usual for ordinary people to make wine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Was she a Halstead person herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, she came from \'85 I think she was born at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Chelmsford
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. You see, previous to coming to Halstead, Father was working for Courtaulds in a mill at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Chelmsford{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 that they had there, where they used to spin the thread. And then that was closed down and he got moved here, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And you were born in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Chelmsford{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, I was born in Halstead.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 To get back to the house. The living}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3539421\charrsid6246232  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 room was on the ground floor, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 That's so, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Can you describe that to me?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 It had quite a nice window in and it was built in the usual style of terraced houses that you find all over \'85
 well, not only Halstead, but I think, generally everywhere in houses built in terraces of that p
eriod, where you got the window up at one side. You see, you came into the back door, which lead into the kitchen and, you see, you had the width of the kitchen where, of course, you \'85
it was impossible to have a window. So the window space was restricted from that portion from the outside wall to the kitchen door. You follow me? So the window was never in the centre or spread along, it was just always in \'85
 you know, the side. So in that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3539421\charrsid6246232 living room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232  there was half the room that you never really got a good li
ght, you see, because the window, in a square that side, the window was always there, or on the opposite row it was, of course, there, you see. So half the room was always in \'85 well, I wouldn't say semi-darkness, but it wasn't very well lit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 What sort of furniture did it have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, there was a fairly large table \'85
 and we wanted it, too, I should have told you that we had 3 aunts, sort of living, like, in the family, who were unmarried then and were also working at Courtaulds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Were they relatives of your mother or your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Of Mother's, yes. And so we wanted a fairly large table, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 So you ate in that room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, we always ate in that room, yes, with the exception of, sort of, high days and holidays when this front roo
m was used. That was kept for special occasions, you see, Christmas, and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3539421\charrsid6246232 living room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 , did you have a fireplace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes, we had an open range, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 But your mother didn't do any cooking on that one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 She did no cooking there at all, no. All the cooking was done in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 In the evenings after you'd had your evening meal, would you sit in that room, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Always, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Were there easy chairs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, there were just the ordinary \'85
 well, Father had an armchair, just ...you know, not upholstered at all, but Mother had made a cushion to sit on and a cushion for the back. He had this chair and then there was a sofa, one of those horsehair things, you know, and then just ordinary chai
rs, you know, just dining}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2457556\charrsid6246232  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 room chairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Were there any bookshelves and books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, there was a little bookshelf there, not a very big one, but \'85 you know, 'Pilgrim's Progress' and books of that nature.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Can you remember the titles of any of the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, there was another one there \'85 'From a Log Cabin to White House'. And then, of course, I had some books, you know, boys' books.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Were those kept with the books in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3539421\charrsid6246232 living room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 They were all, yes, on this little bookshelf 
that hung on the wall. And there were quite a few religious books, too. Father was a Nonconformist and he used to have books on that, and so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Was he a Methodist?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, Congregationalist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And your mother, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And then in the sitting}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2457556\charrsid6246232  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 room, or parlour - what did you call it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 You mean the front room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 We always referred to Kitchen, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3539421\charrsid6246232 Living room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 , and Front room, and that was for special occasions, you know, it was smarter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Can you describe that to me, what was in it and how did it look?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
