\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 One of her employers, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 They are very nice, sort of thing you buy in antique shops now. Were there any pictures?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, there was one or two, again with religious \'85
 religious subjects, such as John Wesley's house on fire, you know, and that sort of thing. He'd got his children round him and making some pronouncement about 'let the house burn, I am rich enough', you know the sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Can you remember if there were any others? That's interesting
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, I can always remember that one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Any photographs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, lots of photographs of the family, you know. Oh, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Where were they standing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 They we
re in frames on the wall, hung on the wall. And, you know, the good ladies had dresses with bustles then, you know, at the back, all \'85 very voluminous sort of \'85 you know, silk things they had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 What was the floor covering?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 The floor covering was 
linoleum, with an odd mat or two which Mother or my aunts used to make themselves with pieces of cloth that they cut off, you know, about 4 inches long, and they threaded them through a net piece.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 A hooked rug?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, that's right. Hat quite a num
ber of them. There'd be a large one in front of the hearth, you see, that would go the whole length of the hearth. They'd work them to a pattern, you know, although they were made from old pieces of cloth which they used to get from tailors and places lik
e that, they would work a design in, same as a diamond in the middle in red, or something like that, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did they work out their own designs, do you think, or did they get one, say, from somebody else, or a shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, they probably copied it, you see. I wouldn't be positive about that. But they had no pattern.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And the floor in the kitchen, what was that? A stone floor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, that was a wooden floor, and again, that was covered in linoleum. In the wash house it was a brick floor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Was there anything else on the ground floor besides those rooms, the front room and the kitchen and the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3539421\charrsid6246232 living room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 You mean any other room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, of course, there was the \'85 the lavatory was outside. The lavatory was between the 
kitchen and the wash house, you see, but of course, you had to go out of the kitchen door to get to the lavatory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 What was on the next floor of your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, well, they were all bedrooms, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Was it a two or three storey house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, two, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 How many bedrooms were there, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, there were 3 bedrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did you have a room on your own, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 I did, there was a little room at the back, you see, over the kitchen. Then in the next room there were the \'85 
there were 2 large beds, and, see, me sister and me aunts slept in them, like, 4 in a room, and then in the front room there was a large bed where Mother and Father lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 There was presumably no bathroom at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Can you tell me what you did about bathing, then when you bathed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
Oh, yes, that was great fun. We used to have a big bath, a big tin bath, and Friday nights was bath night, you see. And we used to have a fire in the wash house and then also the fire under the cop
per, and we used to take our bath in there, you see, and you got plenty of hot water because, like, as \'85
 you know, it was emptied for one bath and filled up again, and heated again, and we had a series of baths on Friday night. That was out method of bathing. I used to think it was, you know, great fun.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Everyone in the family bathed on Friday night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, everyone in the family bathed on Friday night.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did your mother wash the family clothes on one particular day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, always on a Monda
y. Terrific pile. And she also used to do washing, after Father died, she also used to do washing for, you know, other people, like, to earn a shilling or two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did she take it in, or did she go out to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, she used to take it in. I used to \'85
 sometimes I used to go and fetch it and I always took it home to wherever it'd got to go. Sometimes the people concerned used to bring it on a Sunday, Sunday evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 How would you carry it to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, the bundles were not that large so that I couldn't carry it under my arm, sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Have you any idea what they paid her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
Oh, yes, I think she used to get about a shilling a dozen, and a dozen included, you know, big things like sheets and all those sort of things. I don't think that included blankets, but sheets, pillowcases, you know, underclothes, shirts \'85
 all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 You mean that the items were simply counted as single items, irrespective of the size?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 To the best of my knowledge, but obviously, you see,
 you didn't get small things because people who were paying money for that sort of thing, they only sent large things, so you see, you didn't get such things as handkerchiefs. But you used to get things where \'85
 such things as nightdresses where they had al
l these frills and things, and Mother had special irons that were rounded, and that, so as she could go in and these things were cockled up, sort of thing, all done in style. That was a terrific business, you know, ironing, but they all came in, you know,
 that shillings-worth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And so she'd iron them all as well? She'd send them back ironed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes, they were sent back ready for the person to wear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Do you remember where she put the things if she couldn't get them dried outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, they had to hang round, you know, on lines in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3539421\charrsid6246232 living room}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 , in the kitchen, in the wash house. And there was, like, a guard in front of the fire, they used to hang over that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did she iron in the wash house, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, no, she ironed on the dresser, in the kitchen, you see, because \'85
 you see, her iron - she had what was called a 'box iron' and they used heat the piece \'85
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 The piece that you put in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, and then insert it into this box, I reckon, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 So she had to do it on the range, there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Can you tell me about the kind of meals you had, and what did you have for breakfast when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Often porridge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 What type of porridge was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, it was more the Scots type.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 You mean the kind that needs a long cooking, not the Quaker Oats type?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, sometimes the pot was put on overnight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 To cook slowly, you mean, on a very low fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 What did you eat with the porridge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, sometimes we had some jam on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did you have milk on it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
Yes, we used to get plenty of milk because we used to get skimmed milk, you see. We used to go to the farms - there were farms all about - and after they'd removed the cream, the fat, this skimmed milk was sold
 very cheaply. I mean, we used to get, you know \'85 we used to take a quart tin jug and we used to get it very cheaply. I couldn't just say, now, what \'85
 probably a halfpenny or a penny, something like that. I mean, we used to walk, perhaps, a couple of miles to get it. As children quite a lot of us \'85
 it was quite an adventure, like, to go and get the skimmed milk, certain farms we used to go to. It was no trouble hardly because we as children used to like to go. We used to go, in fact, 5 or 6 and we used to g
et this skimmed milk, you know. So we did get milk on the porridge and, of course, if we weren't using jam we had sugar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Anything else for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, no. Oh, for breakfast? Well, we'd have, maybe, bread and butter, or bread and jam, but that was \{illegible\}
, we didn't have any meat, or anything like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Or eggs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Occasionally we used to have an egg between us, when \'85
we couldn't afford to have an egg each, you know, but we used to have one cut in half, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 I have heard of people having a third of an egg, did you ever have one-third?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did you have tea to drink for breakfast when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, yes, tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 As a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, as a child, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Was it very weak tea, or was it quite ordinary tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, that compared favourably with what one would drink today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 I mean, perhaps did they make it very weak when you were a little boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, well, I wouldn't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 What was the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}midday{\*\xmlclose} meal for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
Well, usually it was meat, vegetables, you know, sort of the usual run of potatoes, carrots, turnips and parsnips and cabbage and things of that sort. In the season, of course, peas. Quite a large proportion of them were grown in the garden. And then you'
d finish off with a boiled pudding, fruit puddings when they were in season. 'Course, in the winter - time you had meat puddings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 If you had a meat pudding, would you have another pudding after it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, no, that served as the complete meal along with the vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did you ever start a meal with the pudding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, when we had baked, or {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Yorkshire{\*\xmlclose} pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 But only with that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Then would you have it without anything else, just alone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, you'd have the gravy from the meat on it, you see. It would be served as a separate course, not with your meat and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 But you only did that with the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Yorkshire{\*\xmlclose}?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 But other kinds of puddings you had as a dessert course, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, that's correct.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did you all eat together at dinnertime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, because they were all working at the mill, you see, so the breakfast hours and dinner hours were the same, you see, so therefore \'85

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And they would come home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 They would come home, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And would you, when you started school, come home from school for your dinner, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes, there were no such things as school meals then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 You were near enough to come home, were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, yes, I was only a matter of four of 5 hundred yards away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 How far was the mill away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, the mill was about a quarter of a mile, just a pleasant walk, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Can you tell me, when you had these meals at home, how your mother would organize the meal, and the people and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
Well, we all had a respective place, you know and, of course, everything was ready when we came home because, see, we only used to have three - quarters of an hour for lunch, then, and so it'd got to be sort of ready and, you know, it was \'85
 the pudding and the meat were placed on the table and she allocated each one their portion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 She served up the food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 She served up the food, yes, and usually there was sufficient for a second helping if anybody wanted one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 While you were having your first helping, would she keep it hot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, well, it would be hot, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Where would she put it to keep it hot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, it would be either in the oven, or on top of the register, you know, Oh, yes, always hot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did she serve you in a particular order?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, Father used to be served first, and then it was more or less a question of, you know, sort of \'85
 yes, it would be in a particular order, you know, she got in that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Would the aunts be served before the children, for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, I don't think so. No, I think it was more or less a question of serve it and pass it round, sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Round the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did you have Grace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Not even occasionally, special days, or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No. That's excluding teatime, of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 You had it at teatime, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, we're talking of \'85 I was thinking we were talking of what we call dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 I'm talking about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}midday{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 You called it dinner, when you had your hot dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, we didn't have anything to drink then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Can you remember whether your mother was particularly careful to see whether you ate up all your food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, to my recollection we were all pretty good trencher folk and I don't remember \'85
 later on my sister was a problem, but in those early days, you know, she was robust and, you know, she could eat, and I was the same, and certainly the aunts \'85 I don't think that was really a problem.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 You don't remember her saying you had to finish your plate up or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Do you remember if she was particular about manners at table? For you as a child, do you remember her telling you about table manners?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes. Oh, yes, yes, she always \'85 yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 What sort of things did she think important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, she wouldn't have your elbows on the table, no, she wouldn't. And, you know, you had to use your tools, your utensils \'85
 you know, she wouldn't have your finger in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Was she particular about the way you held the utensils? Or didn't that matter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
Well, no, I don't think she must have been, because I don't think that ever arose. To the best of my knowledge looking back, I think we did handle them, you know, quite well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Were you allowed to talk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
Yes, yes. Occasionally, you know, Father would tell you to sort of shut up, but in the main we were allowed to talk. We weren't restricted, sort of, that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Were you allowed to leave the table when you wanted to, or did you have to wait?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
Oh, no, no. That was one point that they certainly did enforce, that you had to ask permission and you didn't go until you received permission. Oh, yes, that was most important.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And was that usually when everybody else had finished, that you had to wait?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, yes, that was the general rule.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Everyone finished before anyone got down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Anything else you can remember about the way she taught you manners at table? Were you allowed to ask for second helpings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
Oh, yes, oh, yes. You know, often if you didn't ask Mother would offer it, you see. You know, 'come on, have another piece of this', that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 On Sundays did you have a special dinner? Was it different in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, rather, because for one thing, you see, you always had a roast. You see, you had a larger joint and then, of course, that did serve 
\'85 that came up again on Monday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 As cold?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, as cold.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 For {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute
}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}midday{\*\xmlclose} dinner?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Do you remember whether she had any particular kind of joints, or did she have beef and lamb and pork, that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, it would be \'85it would vary, you know, sometimes we'd have beef, sometimes mutton. Occasionally, you know a
 small leg of pork. It varied, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did she roast potatoes with the joint?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
Not very often, no, not very often. It was rare to have the potatoes roasted, they were usually boiled and had, you know, in the wintertime they were mashed, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did you have any special kind of puddings? If you had beef I suppose you had the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Yorkshire
{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 We had the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Yorkshire{\*\xmlclose}
, yes, that's right. And then on a Sunday sometimes we'd have a sweet pudding as well. Or failing that, a fruit tart, or a currant tart or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Would she have baked on a Saturday? Did she have a baking day for the weekend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
Well, she bakes sometimes twice a week, you know, but Saturday would be one of the days when she would bake, you know, not only for dinner, but the usual pies and tarts and things that one had for tea, or buns and cakes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 When you said a sweet pudding for dinner on a Sunday, what type of sweet pudding would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, such things as a ginger pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 A ginger sponge pudding, you mean, that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 With custard, did she make custard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
Very rarely. We did have it sometimes. We used to just eat it on its own. And there was pudding with currants in, Spotted Dick I think it was called. And there was another type, similar to \'85
 well, it was like a Yorkshire pudding but with currants and sultanas in. I believe they call it Nelson's cake now, or something like that, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Anything made of chocolate, or cocoa?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, I don't recall them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 What about fresh fruit, did you ever have anything made with fresh fruit?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
Sorry, I didn't really mean made of fruit because you already mentioned tarts and things like that. Did you ever have the fresh fruit uncooked, you know, like an apple?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Not with the meal, no. Not with the meal. Plenty, you know, in between meals, but not served with the meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Not as a desert?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did you ever have cheese at the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}midday{\*\xmlclose} meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 What did you have to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Sometimes water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Anything else, tea or coffee?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Then the next meal of the day was tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 The next meal of the day was tea, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 What time was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 About a {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 17}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname 
Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 15}}}quarter past 5{\*\xmlclose}, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 17}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}}half past 5{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And that was when you came home from...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 When we came home from work, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 What did you have for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
Well, that used to vary. I mean, sometimes we used to have some fish, sometimes a bloater, or a kipper. Or, you used to get, in those days, sprats. There was quite a variety of \'85
 usually, apart from the bread and butter, jam or a piece of cheese, there was usually the addition of one of these things, you see, or \'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Fish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Or maybe lettuce, or tomato. There was usually, like, an addition to, like, the ordinary te
a, and, of course, there was always a cake of some sort, all made at home, of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And tea to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And tea to drink, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 You had the same as a child, did you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 When you were a very small child, before you went to school, would you have that same meal with the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Pretty well, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 You ate together at all meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Didn't have any patent foods, anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 I meant to ask you, actually, about breakfast. Did the whole family have breakfast together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, yes, because they all started at the same time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Would they have started, and then come back for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, they used to start at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}6 o'clock{\*\xmlclose}, you see, and then come back at a quarter past 8 'till {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 9}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}9 o'clock{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 So breakfast was at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 What about when you were at school, did you have breakfast then before you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 But also with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Was that tea the last food you had in the day, or did you have anything before you went to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
Well, we did used to have something for supper, not a sit-down meal, but we used to have sometimes a glass of milk, sometimes a cup of cocoa. More often cocoa than just milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did you have meat most days of the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Y
es, I don't recall a dinner without meat of some sort. Because there was a wide variety, I mean, there was all the offals, and things, you know, the livers and all those sort of things. Kidneys. But we always had meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 The fruit you mentioned, would you have that in between meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes, I mean, come in and get an apple any time, or greengages, or plums.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 All, again, from the garden, were they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 So you had a pretty good diet, by the sound of things. A balanced diet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Ac
tually, we did. Although we were poor, we were always fed well. I never remember wanting food and couldn't have it, you know. Very, very fortunate in that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Do you think your mother was a particularly good manager?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Extraordinary, yes, she was a most capable manager.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 She obviously was a very good cook, because a lot of people didn't even know how to cook things like offal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes. My father was very proud of her cooking, you know. I mean, he wasn't a man who had a lot to say, but he
 was very proud of her cooking. She was a very capable housewife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did you ever have a glass of milk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, we had a mug of milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 You had that at teatime, or in between.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 In between, mostly. We never used to have it in place of tea, or anything like that. And this cocoa was very regular for supper, you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Do you remember how your mother shopped? Did she go to the shops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, she used to go to the shop. No, I'm sorry, she used to send an order in. A man used to come from the 
village grocer, or the town grocer, and take her order and that used to be delivered during the week in a box. Because we always used to wait for that to come, because that was a custom that with each order the grocer used to put a little packet of boiled
 sweets in for the children, you see. So, you see, that was very important to us and we used to wait 'till \'85 I think it was Mr. Seymour's man, and he used to bring this little packet of sweets, you see. That used to be ours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And what about the butcher, did she have an order sent there, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, she usually used to go and get her meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did she do all her shopping in Halstead?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes, all in Halstead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did she have anybody doing errands for her? In the way of shopping and anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
Well, sometimes we would. Sometimes we would run errands and...It wasn't necessary for her to have anyone else because we were always around, you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did your father actually do anything to help, actually in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, no, I don't think he did, other than \'85 he used to, you know, chop wood, light the fire. He used to do the garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did he just do the kitchen fire, or did he do any other fires as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, he used to do the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3539421\charrsid6246232 living room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232  fire as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And clean out the grate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No! Oh, no, no, he wouldn't do that. He would prepare the fuel for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 But she would actually clean the grate and make the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 She would clean the grate, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Do you remember whether you had any particular kind of a job to do in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes, on Saturdays I used to be responsible for cleaning the knives and spoons. You see \'85
 as you know, there were no stainless ones then and we used to have some powder, like dust powder, sort of Monkey Brand style, if you
 know what that was, you know, the usual sort of ground stone and fine powder and we used to rub it all up, you know, until we'd got all the stains of it, so they used to shine. It didn't last long 'cos soon as they went into any acid or anything like tha
t they were stained again. But that was a regular Saturday job. Then we used to have a white powder for doing the spoons and folks, a kind of whitening, you know, I used to sort of have to do them. And that was my\'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 When you say 'we', was that you and your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, that's right. And then the aunts used to do it as well, sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Were they quite young, the aunts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, they were older than us, you see, naturally, but not all that old, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Younger than your mother, or older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Younger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did you do any boot cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes, yes, they used to \'85 well, you used to have to clean your own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes. Oh, yes, I mean, you had to go to school with them \'85 Sometimes Father used to clean them, but in 
the main, you know, you were responsible for your own.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And that was with a sort of black lead stuff, was it, blacking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, that wasn't polish, you know, it was \'85 you sort of put this black lead on and let it dry and then, you know, you used to
 get a shine on that way. Blacking they used to call it, blacking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did you do anything in the garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Not a lot, no, not while Father was alive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 He did the garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did your mother ever have anybody helping her in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, the aunts used to help her. They had jobs to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Was she a very organized sort of person? I mean, did they have set things to do, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes, yes. She was the boss, you know. She was the boss in her sphere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 How did your father and your mother manage their money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, he used to give her \'85 I don't know just what it was, and so she paid the bills.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And then he'd keep something back for his own needs, would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, he was a frugal liver in that w
ay, I mean, he had his beer, as I told you, his glass, but one glass a day, no more and no less, you know. It was a ritual, like, and he used to smoke. He loved his pipe, and that was about all he wanted money for, to buy tobacco. And then, of course, all
 the rest went into the home, and for children's clothes }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248386 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 c.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did your mother belong to clubs? For saving for clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 What about insurance, and that sort of thing. Do you remember if they belonged to clubs \'85?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, yes, she used to pay into \'85
 or rather Father was a member of the Friendly Society, the Foresters Society and he used to contribute to that. And that, of course, entitled them to, sort of, a doctor. And I think she paid a very small premium to the Pearl Insurance Company. 
That was a man who'd come to the door and they'd pay something like about a penny a week, or probably it might have been less, you know. And in the event of death that entitled them to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248386 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 8 or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248386 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 9, something like that, you know. Hardly enough to bury anyone, 
you know, but that was all that, you know, she contributed to.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 If she wanted to buy a particular article of clothing did she save up herself for the money, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes, she had to, yes. And then, as I said, she did use this co-operative dividend, you see. Such things as coal, bread, not milk \'85
 coal, bread, and some groceries, anything like that, you see, she got from the Co-Op\'85 clothes and, you see, there was a dividend paid on everything, and then when she wanted something special, li
ke, in the way of clothes, or something she'd got to get for the house, or household linen, something like that, then it used to come from this dividend, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And you think it was all from the dividend, anything sort of special she wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, yes. Yes, because, you see, she never had any money. Every shilling, you know, had to be scraped together, like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 One thing I didn't ask you last week was your father's occupation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 He was a factory labourer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 What was the factory?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 The silk factory, Courtaulds silk factory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 What kind of work did he do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
Well, it was really conveying the rolls of silk or what we call the beams - what they call the beams - which was a large roll of silk, from one machine to another one \'85 warping machines. You know what a warp is, don't you? You have the, sort of \{BLANK
\} that take the cross threads. Well, they were very heavy, on very heavy and of course, there wasn't the lifting tackle that, you know, one has today. Most of it had to be manhandled, and when these things were \'85
 they were heavy in themselves, they were \'85 sort of \'85 made of \'85 you know heavy oak and reinforced with steel and then when they'd got the silk, the length of silk on as well they were extremely heavy. And it was his j
ob to sort of take them out of one machine and sort of put them in another for another process.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did he do that type of work all his working life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, no, no. Previous to \'85 I believe I did mention to you that previous to that he had been a factory foreman at 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Chelmsford{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. Courtaulds had a silk-throwing mill there and then it was closed down and all they could offer him was a job at Halstead, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 About what age was he then, when he came to Halstead?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh when he came to Halstead he'd be - what? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2457556\charrsid6246232 - 35, forty-ish.}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And did he ever become a foreman again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
No, no. Actually, I don't think I mentioned it to you that on that particular job here he strained his heart which was, you know, due to lifting heavy weights, and he was invalided and he died of this trouble when he was 54.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 I know you mentioned that your mother had lived longer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, that's correct. The doctor said, like, that if it had been a weak heart, or even a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2457556\charrsid6246232 diseased}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232  heart that he could have patched him up, but 
with the valves of his heart strained like that there was nothing - at least in those days, there was nothing they could do about it, and so he died, as I say, at 54.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 What age was he when he was invalided out of the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, he was over 50. Oh, yes, he was over 50, he didn't last many years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And do you know if in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Chelmsford{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, before he was working at Courtaulds there, had he had any other work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, I can't \'85 I couldn't recall if he had another job, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 You mentioned when you were showing me those pretty }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2457556\charrsid6246232 lustre}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232  cups that your mother's family had been in service. Had your mother herself been in service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, she had been in service. She was in service in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} with a family of tailors.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 What was her particular domestic work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 I couldn't tell you whether she was, you know, sort of a housemaid or a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2457556\charrsid6246232 
kitchen maid}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 , or a cook. I really couldn't tell you, but in a way she \'85 I've heard her say that, you know, she had quite an interesting time in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. She apparently was with a good family. And she also had an uncle or two in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} who, you know, used to keep an eye on her and \'85 'cos she was a young girl when she was there. And they used to take her down to the City because two of them had jobs, kind of caretaker in City offi
ces, you see, and they used to take her down, and take her up into these blocks of offices and apparently, you know, they really did show her around. So although she was a servant girl she did, you know, get quite a knowledge of that part of 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And your sister - while we're on occupations - did she have a job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, my sister was a weaver down at Courtaulds until she married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 After she married did she go back to work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, no. No, she's living at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Braintree{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}, now. But actually she wouldn't have been able to work anyway, because soon after marrying she had an attack of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2457556\charrsid6246232 colitis}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232  and she had a long period of getting this sort of \'85 you know \'85 well, at least, coming to terms with it, and so that would have precluded work, in any case.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 I also wanted to ask you how much you saw of your father? Did you spend any time with him as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
No, not a lot of time. In fact, he always seems like an old man to me. He was a kind man, but the relationship was never close in that sense, you know. Remote.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 You didn't confide in him, tell him how you felt, that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Never \'85 no, I never \'85
 you know, I never recall confiding in Father. Mother, yes, but never Father. And yet he was a kind man. As far as one can tell, you know, a good man. But there was never a close relationship between us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Was the same true of your sister, do you think, or was she closer? Girls sometimes are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, of course, she was very young, you see, so I don't think she \'85 when he died she was very y
oung, she wouldn't really have been able to appreciate the relationship between them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 You don't have recollections of him playing with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Do you remember any jealousy of your sister as far as her closeness to your father was concerned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, no, never, no. To the best of my recollection \'85
 mind you, you see, like, he was an ill man soon after me sister was born and that wouldn't make for \'85 you know, an intimate sort of association. He was, you see, bedridden for a long time,
 and all those conditions, you see, would exclude normal family relations, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Do you think that he was a reserved man with most people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 He was a reserved man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 It was in his character to be like that, it wasn't just as a father that he was reserved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 I remember you said he didn't go to public houses and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, no, he \'85
 I suppose one would say, judged in those terms, that he lived a good life. Always somewhat remote from us, you know. Not neglectful.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 I know just what you mean. And your sister, were you and she close?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, yes, we were close. And we remain so today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Do you remember quarrelling with her a lot, or did you get on pretty well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, we got along pretty well, and then, you see, I was 12 years older than her, and in a way \'85 sort of \'85
 when Father died, like I more or less sort of had to take the place, you see, she head of the \'85 sort of, the family, so there was a peculiar relationship there. And anyway, I always li
ked kath and, you know, anything that I did, it gave me pleasure and that's the relationship that exists even today, although she's, you know, married, and has a family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Do you remember any kind of outings or excursions with your father at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes, yes. We would go down to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Yarmouth{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} on a factory excursion, when they used to run a day excursion when we had a railway, you see. They used to run a special train and we used to go to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Yarmouth
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. That was an annual, sort of outing, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Was that for the families of the men employed there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, that would be for the employees and their families.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 So your mother would go, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And what about any other outings, did you ever go out together on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Sometimes we used to go to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2457556\charrsid6246232 Bocking}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232  to visit \'85 he had some brothers there at Bocking, and that's 5 miles from here, you see. And that was quite an adventure because, you see, there was no means of getting to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Braintree{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} by train on a Sunday, see. It would have been possible by a very devious route on any other day to have gone, sort of, via Marks Tey back to Witham, and then from Witham to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Braintree{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, but of course, that was out of the question on a Sunday. And consequently, the only means of getting to Bocking and 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Braintree{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} was by a horse waggonette. And this particular waggonette that we used to go by, it was about \'85
 one horse, you know, and with a driver up the front, and it was a sort of a canvas contraption where you sat, you know, sort of 4 one side and 
4 the other. And there was a little candle lamp at the end, just behind the driver and when we were coming back - it used to go in the morning and then return, you know, about 7 o'clock or something, in the evening, and we used to pick it up, having been 
down to Bocking, we used to pick it up at the \{illegible\}
 on the main road, and there'd be just this little glimmer - it'd be dark and there was just this little glimmer of a candle, you see, and then when you were sort of safely in your seats and there wou
ld be no more stops until you got to Halstead, he used to snuff the candle out, you see, so you sat in complete darkness until you got to the top of the hill at Halstead. Then he used to stop at. The pigeon's pub and he used to light his little candle aga
in and so there was a glimmer of light for you as you come down the market for Halstead, and that, you know, remained quite an adventure.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And your mother, did she have any friends or people she had social activities with outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 She had friends, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And of course, she had her 3 sister, didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes. Well, of course, they all married \'85 I mean, they married soon after the death of Father, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 What was the year of your father's death?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 1912. Let me see, now, l
et's be sure. Sorry, 1910. You see, my aunts, they all married and then, of course, they left home and set up home on their own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Do you remember their weddings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, I can remember them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Were they married from your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Two of them were, yes. One was married in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Yorkshire{\*\xmlclose}
. But I recall them. I recall, you know, a couple of uncles coming home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 When your father died, did you wear black?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes. Oh, yes, I well remember that all the \'85 that must have been a great sacrifice. Mo
ther bought me a new dark grey suit. I don't know how she did it, but that was so. And I think to the best of my recollection about all my father left, apart from his home, was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2248386 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 9. You see, he'd been ill and what little money - which was only a few pounds - he'd had to draw upon, you see. I think that was the sum total of everything that Mother had, was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2248386 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 9.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And what about any debts, were there any debts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, no, she never had any debts. As a matter of fact, going back to that suit I had, she real
ly had a real fright, because that suit was paid for, and about a year afterwards she had the bill come in again, and I suppose that was, you know, two or three pounds, and how on earth \'85
 I mean, she was really up against it then, a year afterwards. And th
at really was a great headache for her and she could not find the receipted bill and she had some anxious times. But she did find it eventually. And that was an error on the tailor's part, but you can just imagine, like how she felt receiving this bill af
ter all that time, and having no money. But never any debts. She would not \'85 at no time, you know, did she ever incur any debt of any sort. Really wonderful that way.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 With your grey suit did you wear any actual black at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, no. I had a black tie, you know, a little black thing on a piece of elastic. It was a stiff sort of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2457556\charrsid6246232 rubberised}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232  little collar thing and this little black bow thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Was the suit specifically for the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes, yes. Of course, mind you I had to wear it for the rest\'85
 that was my Sunday suit, but that was, you know, so that we should all be respectable when we went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did you wear any black of any kind, either an armband or a tie, after the funeral for any period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, I didn't wear \'85 I wore the tie o
n Sundays, but that was probably 'cos it was new and because I'd got it, sort of thing. But I didn't have a black armband, although that was the custom in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Do you think it was perhaps because of your age that you didn't wear one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, yes, that was it because what was I? 11.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
And the aunts and your mother, did they change their clothing at all after your father's death? Or had they been wearing black before anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, no, they changed their clothes. They did have a black outfit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And your mother wore that, did she, after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 She wore that, of yes. Not continuously, but Sundays, for the, you know..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 But not for the ordinary day to day wear?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, no! Oh, no. She wore her usual clothes. Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 This is interesting because with people with money at that time morning was still very much the usual thing in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}England{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, but you think it wasn't so with poorer people because they just couldn't afford it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, no! No, no, no. I should say that if they had black, well it was just happened to be that that was probably the only thing \'85
 dress, frock, that they had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Do you remember the funeral? Did you go to the funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 I've got a recollection of the funeral. I mean, there was a couple of uncles there from Bocking. And I recall \'85
 one of my uncles from Bocking, he read the Will, and - because Father had made a Will - and it was just as well that he had, because I had another uncle who was working in London and \'85 this was Mother's version, like. He quite expect
ed, like, sort of with the death of Father that the home sort of might be broken up, sort of thing. And, of course, the Will clearly stated that in fact, you know, what he had, home and everything, was left to Mother and that was that. But, you know, Moth
er always had a feeling that this uncle from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 thought, well, you know, the home would be sold up and that sort of thing. So she was greatly relieved that there was no possibility of that sort of thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Was there any kind of family gathering? You know, a meal together, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes, there was a meal afterwards. Yes, oh, yes. I mean, that was the custom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 All sitting down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 A hot meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, that wasn't, no. That was what you would call a high tea. Do you know what I mean by a high tea? Some cold meat and \'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Tea and bread and butter and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, and cake.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Anything alcoholic to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, no, there was only tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 It was a sad and serious affair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 It was, real
ly. And, I mean, Mother did realise that it was going to be a pretty hard struggle for her, you see, and so there was no suggestion of a party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Can you tell me, then, after your father's death, did your mother go out to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 She did try working at the silk factory but, you see, she'd never been in a factory. As I mentioned she was in service in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, and she didn't take kindly to factory life. I mean it was something totally alien to what she'd \'85
 you know, been used to, and consequently she left there. And then she \'85 my aunts by that time \'85
 they married within months, they'd gone, you know, to set up their homes, wherever they were going. And so Mother then used to take in this washing that I told you about. She also used to go out and do house
work for some old people who could probably pay her a shilling, something like that. And then eventually.. and I believe I mentioned it to you before \'85
 she did take as lodgers some if the girls who came into the town to work at Courtaulds, and she continued for years and years, like, with these girls.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 It was a weekly boarding system, wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, they used to go home on the Saturday morning and then return on the Sunday evening. Most of them came from 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Haverhill{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, the town where they .. they us
ed to weave there, but for another firm and pay hadn't been too good and so Courtaulds, you know, offered them work here and they came here, and so Mother used to lodge them all the week, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did they live with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, they had the same meals and they lived with us, yes, exactly the same as we lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Was it a lot of extra work for your mother, having them, do you thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, it was, because, see, there were more meals to provide for, and there was all the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2457556\charrsid6246232 bed linen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232  which had to be, you know, changed, and that sort of thing, the usual things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did she do any other washing for them besides the linen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, no, they used to take it home with them, you see, and their parents, I suppose, used to do it for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did she do their rooms and make the beds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes, yes, everything. They didn't make their own beds. Well, you see, they had to go off at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}6 o'clock{\*\xmlclose} in the morning. At least, commence work at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname 
Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}6 o'clock{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did they help her at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes, they were g
ood girls. Actually, I think without exception, to my recollection of them - although I didn't see as much of them as my sister did, because, you see, the War came along and I was involved in that, you see. But they were a good type of girl and I don't th
ink on any occasion, you know, they ever gave her any trouble in that sense, you know, they were decent, honest sort of working folk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 They helped with washing up and they didn't expect to be waited on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes. I think, as far as I can recollect, almost without exception they were all decent girls. Those that I knew certainly were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 You don't, I suppose, know what they paid her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 I couldn't \'85 no, I couldn't, but it was shillings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 There wasn't a lot of money in it for the work involved?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 They would have had so little themselves, wouldn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, and they had their expenses, too, train expenses to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}
Haverhill{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 How did the death of your father, and your mother having to do this sort of work aff
ect the standard of living of the family? Was the food less plentiful?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No! Mother, somehow or other, you know, \'85 we just fed as well as ever, because she always insisted on that, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 She was a wonderful manager, wasn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 She was, oh, yes, yes. So really, we didn't suffer in any way that way. I mean, she did put that first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Were there other ways you think you suffered, in comparison with what had been before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, there were things like the little extras, I mean, my frie
nds then were joining the scout movement, you see, and I would have loved to have joined the scout movement. That would have meant paying for a little bit of uniform, and that sort of thing. Well, you know, that was out, you see. My schoolmaster, he wante
d me to sit for the examination to the Grammar school, you see. There was just \'85
 very little was paid then, but again, you see, that would have meant another shilling, say, per day, and a certain amount of uniform - a cap and a satchel, things like that, an
d that was out. And so it was in relation to things like that, you see, that we just had to do without. Mother did her best to feed us and clothe us, and she used to make a lot of clothes. She had a hand sewing machine which she used to use 'till past 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}midnight{\*\xmlclose}
 when, you know, all the rest of us had gone to be she used to be sitting down there making clothes, and that, for us. So it was in relation to things like that, shall I say the extras, you know, that we just had to do without.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Do you remember whether you were very disappointed not to be able to sit this entrance exam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes. Yes, because I'd always been very much interested in \'85
 well, in what little smattering you got at an elementary school, you know, in those days in sort of cultural thi
ngs, you know. Little bit of, you know, sort of poetry, sort of little smattering of, you know, sort of Greek history, and things like that, which was very little, but \'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Whetted your appetite for more, did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes, yes, I would have loved it
, you know, but that's just how it was, you see. I mean, as soon as I became 13, well, I had an economic value of half a crown a week, and you could leave school then, you see, at 13, and that's what happened, you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Can you tell if, before you left school and started earning full-time, you earned any money in any small jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 I used to do one or two little jobs, you know, for people. Sort of, clean their knives and forks on a Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 As well as your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 As well as our own. Well, that was in the usual chores, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 What would they pay you for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 About 2d., something like that; 2d., all helpful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Anything else besides that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 You didn't do any errand work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, I didn't do any errand work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did you get any pocket money at any time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, yes, sometimes I used to get a halfpenny, or even a farthing, because you could buy a little sort of sweet, you know, for a farthing.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 You don't remember getting this as a regular thing, though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
No, not as a regular thing, no. And of course, in relation to doing any other job, you see, with this additional washing that Mother used to do for other people, we used to help her out with turning this mangle, you know. It was one of these old, 
big sort of manual things, you know, with a big wheel and as she was, you know, sort of putting them through we used to turn the handle for her. Both me and, you know, my sister, sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did your mother have any activities outside the home? Clubs, or anything of that sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, she did \'85 she attended the Chapel on Sunday, but she had no other activities. She hadn't any spare time in that sense, you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And what she saw of people, was that mostly visiting? You said that she did have friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, she had friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 In what circumstances would she see these friends and exchange news?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
On Sundays, Sunday evening after Chapel, they would have a walk, taking my sister when she was younger and they used to walk the fields. I mean, they'd go sort of \'85 over to neighbouring villages and sort of.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Would your father go too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Early on, yes, but I was thinking more or less after he died, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Early on it would have been both of them having a walk after \'85?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Quite, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And after your father died, she'd go for a walk, perhaps with a woman friend, would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
That's so, yes, yes, and she had one particular friend who was very interested in my sister, who was childless and who used to make rather a fuss of
 my sister and so they used to walk with her. And then sometimes they used to take my sister out with them. You know, they had bicycles, which was quite a possession, like, for working people then, and they used to ride to Colchester, and around that area
 
they had relatives and they used to take my sister on a sort of a business at the back, sort of thing. And so she used to visit around Bentley, and that sort of thing, you know. They were very kind to my sister, and me, too, in a way, but particularly att
racted by my sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did you have a bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, no, not until I was \'85
 Oh, I never had a bicycle until I came out of the forces in the World War I, you know. Oh, no, I couldn't afford a bicycle. But I had a neighbour who had one and sometimes he 
would loan it to me and so I was able to, you know, sort of go out with some of my friends who were more fortunate than me. But I never had a bicycle until I came out of the forces in .. end of 1919.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And your mother, did she ever have one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No! It was beyond the realms of possibility.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 So everywhere she went she walked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did she live pretty near the shops? And the things she needed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, she lived \'85 yes, in 7 minutes of the shops. Well, 10 minutes, we'll say, 10 minutes of the shops, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 You said that your father didn't go to public houses, did he have a working man's club, or any institutes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, no. He was a man who was quite contented in his home, and he had his garden; and he used to read his Bible. H
e was not a sanctimonious man, but \'85
 We only had one sort of paper or magazine about the house and that was the Christian Herald which, you know, did have some general news in as well as, you know, religious sort of news, and this Christian Herald was the 
only newspaper that we had in the house.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did you have any books? Oh, yes, I remember you telling me that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Of course, in addition to that there was such things as 'Black Beauty', they were my books, books that had been given to me, and 'Tom Brow
n's Schooldays', and things of that sort, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Was your father in a trade union, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Do you remember family or friends coming to the house for tea or for meals, at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes. Oh, yes, some of his, you know, friends from the Chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 What day of the week would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, it was always Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 What time would they come, roughly speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Come in the afternoon and we used to have a, you know, general talk about things, and then have this meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 What sort of meal would that be when people came in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, well, that was, like, a little special, there'd be, like, \'85
 well, Sunday tea we usually had a little extra, you know, and that would be on that occasion, you know. Mother would produce something, you know, such things as sausage rolls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 It would be a cold tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, it would be cold, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 You mentioned that sometimes during the week you'd have a bit of fish in the evening, would you have that on a Sunday as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, not on a Sunday, no, never have fish on a Sunday. That was a \'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Cold meat would you have had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
Yes, we should sometimes have some cold beef off the Sunday joint, and also, you know, a piece of cold pork. It was possible to get slices of that from a pork.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And that glass of beer your father used to have, would his friends have had one of those, too?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, no, that only \'85 to the best of my knowledge that only was produced for Father's supper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 So at this tea it would have been tea to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 It was tea to drink, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 The people who came in, would they bring children with them? Or was it an adult affair, this tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 In the main they were adults, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Do you remember yourself ever having friends in to tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh
, yes. Oh, yes, and we had birthday parties and a Christmas party. Oh, yes, quite a feature, I mean, they'd save up, I'd say, for months to have a birthday party and you'd have, perhaps, 7 or 8 of your friends there. When I say 'friends', children in the 
road where we lived, you see, you know, round about your age. Oh, yes, that was \'85
 and there was, you know, great preparation, paper chains hung about. And on that special occasion there would be a few nuts and oranges, not a whole orange, you know. The oran
ge would be cut into sort of quarters. Then, of course, there were apples, which, of course, we had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 You are talking now of Christmas and birthday parties? Was it much the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Would you have a cake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, oh, yes, Mother made cakes, she was a good cake maker, and \'85
 It wouldn't be iced or anything, but it was, you know, a good fruit cake.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did you play any games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes, there was this sort of 'Ring a Ring o' Rosie' business and such things as that, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did you have those parties even after your Father died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes, yes. Oh, yes, Mother somehow or other, she \'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 She managed to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 She did that. Mind you, she was \'85 although it meant all that work, and scraping the money together 
and all that, she enjoyed it, you know. She got pleasure out of it, 'cos she was a gay person. She had a wonderful \'85
 in spite of her difficulties, you know, thinking of her now, you know, she really had a joy of living, in spite of hard work and graft and that sort of thing. When I mention 'graft', I mean hard work. She got a great kick out of events like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 She liked to see other people enjoying themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes, and she could enjoy herself, too, in her way. I think that was one of her gr
eatest assets, when I come to think of it. She worked hard and she would play hard if she got an opportunity.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 At the birthday parties, did children bring presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, yes, they would bring a little present, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And did the parents give presents, too, to their own child, and were birthday presents given by the family to the child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes. You mean would Mother give us a present?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes, yes, that was always done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Do you remember giving your parents and your sister presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 When you said you saved up for this party, did you have to save your own halfpennies and pennies for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, I was thinking of Mother. She would, like, when the party was coming off she would order on her goods, lik
e, perhaps a few shillings this week and, you know, something else next week, so gradually she collected sufficient to have this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Do you remember any discussion in the home about politics, or religion, or current events, that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes,
 Father was a Liberal, a Nonconformist and of course, that was very strong Chapel. That Liberal, sort of nonconformist tradition, you know, and he was sort of in that and he was a very strong Liberal. Of course, then there was just Conservative or Liberal
. But there was then a branch of the independent Labour Party just being formed here and \'85
 oh, Father had got no time for them because it was said that they were atheists, you see and, of course, that in itself put them beyond the pale, and of course, he wouldn't have been a man who would have associated himself with trade unionism, you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 He would have disapproved of it, would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 I think he would, yes, yes. I think he'd got that old attitude of, you know, the master knows best. Without being 
subservient, but I don't think he could have visualized, you know, a new order of that sort. That's the impression that I got. I mean, obviously, he never discussed those things with me, but I can imagine, like, with his Chapel associates and that, they w
ouldn't have had any time for that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And you and Mr. Spurgeon have been friends for - when you were children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No. No, I didn't \'85.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 You would have know of him because he was a well-known man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, and I'm sure, like, he wouldn't have approved of him because they were \'85
 you know, I knew Reggie's father latterly and, you know, they were \'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Different views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 You know, different type of person altogether, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And your mother, do you think that her views on society, politics and religion were similar to your father's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, no! Oh, dear, dear, no. No, no, no. No, she was \'85 she was, in my opinion, you know, progressive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 At that time, too, do you think she was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, she hadn't much time, then, I mean, people like her \'85
 I mean, certainly like a woman's position, a working woman's position, a part from the fact that she was too preoccupied with, you know, living, making a do of things to give any time to that, but she had an independence of mind and so as things p
rogressed she was able to move from the accepted idea of Chapel-going and Liberal parties, to something which she considered more progressive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Would that have been after your father's death, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes, yes, some time after Father's d
eath. It might have been accentuated by the fact that, you know, her hard struggle itself. And the fact that, she was \'85
 she had an independent mind, you know, I think all that tended to make her, you know, look at things. And she would express herself on those things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
Was she quite a talkative person? I mean, did she like discussions about things? You know, when you were a child do you remember her discussing things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, not unduly, but she certainly \'85 you know, she certainly, latterly, like \'85 Wh
en she had more time to study things, and we did get more information and that then, she was quite a keen student of \{illegible\}
. And I think there'd always been that sort of element in the family. She told me that she had an uncle - I think it was one of 
those that she used to meet in London when she was a young girl - who was a very great reader, and she used to talk about when he took her to his flat, you know, his wonderful collection of books and had she had time and that sort of thing, I'm sure that,
 you know, she would have loved to have studied herself, you know. She had a great reverence for those books, you know, and she used to talk \'85 and she said \'85
 oh, she told me several times, like, you know, all his money he used to spend on books, this uncle, you know, and I could see the way she spoke about it, you know, she regular \'85 sort of \'85
 revered him, like. Oh, no, she tried to keep in the van of things, after getting over those hard years when, you know, she \'85 the great thing was to, you know, fight and keep us and feed us well and, you know, sort of make a living like I said.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Do you remember her actually reading to you, reading aloud to you when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, no, I don't. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 But both your parents did read and write?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes. Oh, yes. Mother had to pay to go to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 When she was a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, they had to pay \'85 I think it was about 3d., I think it was, and they had to provide their own books and their writing material.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 When you were at school, do you remember your parents taking an interest, I mean expressing an interest in your schooling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes. Oh, yes, yes. Yes, I mean, we used to get a school report, you know, and they used to, you know, be very interested in that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 What were their views on discipline?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
Well, that wasn't a great problem, not in our life. I mean, if we sort of did anything which they considered wrong, I mean, Mother would clout us, but it was salutary, you know, and \'85 When I say 'clout us', you know, I mean a clip of 
the ear, something like that, but nothing vicious. That served the purpose for the time and you might call it old fashioned discipline, but I think that was, you know, effective. I mean, we knew \'85 we respected it. No such things as }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2457556\charrsid6246232 striking}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232  \'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 What about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 He was a \'85 he would express his disapproval, but \'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 It was she who actually carried out the punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, I never saw him \'85 I don't remember him striking any of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No beatings with a brush, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, no, no, no. Now, I do remember there was a cane hung up there, but never \'85
 it was never used. I think that was more of a threat. No, that was never used, and never a stick or anything like that, but I do remember a cane hanging there, but it was never used.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Do you remember any other type of punishment? Being deprived of anything or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, I don't think so, the only depriving was, you know, because of economic causes, you know, I mean things we couldn't have and couldn't 
do and our friends, you know, and mates who'd got fathers at work had. This was about the only \'85
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 You don't remember being sent to bed early or deprived of any sort of treat of any sort because you'd done something wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, I don't \'85 I can reca
ll many a time Mother threatening my sister. She was very much concerned with - what shall I say? - being shown up, because my sister sometimes would do things which I suppose Mother thought ought not to be done in company, and I've heard her say, 'now, l
ook here, my girl, we don't so-and-so and so-and-so, and don't you show me up'. Now, 'show me up' might have been \'85
 well, it was doing something which Mother thought she ought not to do, you see. You know, it might have been, you know, answering someone imp
olitely or something like that. But she used to read the riot act over her, you see, and she'd threaten her with all sorts of dire things if she showed her up. But I don't think it ever came to that, but I can recall my sister receiving that lecture befor
e they set out. That was, as I say, showing her up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Was your mother particular about good manners and courteous behaviour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes, she was very particular about that, yes. And a part from her own upbringing, which I should think was petty good f
or a working family, you see, she had been in service in a good family and that in itself would tend to lay the stress on good manners. Although, as sort of working people, I mean they were all good that way. I recall my uncles and cousins at \'85
 or one cousin at Bocking that we used to \'85 you know, they were people like that, you know, who \'85 again, as I say, they would be what \'85
 they would be called God fearing people, whatever that means, and they did keep a decent standard. And Mother was most insistent, you know, that that should be maintained, even in our comparative poverty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Do you remember whether she was particular about how you greeted people who came into the house, or how you said good-bye?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes, oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Answering when you were spoken to, or not speaking, that type of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, that all came within that sphere of, shall I say, not showing her up, you see. Doing the correct thing, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 I wonder if you can remember any specific instances of the type of behaviour she
 demanded in that way, because fashions change so much in what children are expected to do now. What children are expected to do now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, I don't think I can give you a specific \'85 you know, it was a general sort of thing that I was thinking of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Were you expected to talk to adults?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Would it have been considered rude if you'd initiated a conversation with an older person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, I don't think that would have been considered rude, like with sort of friends who used to 
take in interest in us, and that, I think it was welcomed, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 At meals you were allowed to talk, I think I remember you saying?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, yes, at meals we could talk, oh, yes. But we had to pay regard to table manners, I mean, for instance we w
eren't allowed to put elbows on the table. We weren't allowed to get down before, you know, the meal was finished unless we got permission by other members of the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Do you remember if Sunday was strictly kept when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, y
es, but not to the point of sort of absurdity, like, in the sense that we went to Sunday School, and then from Sunday School into Chapel. Father went Sunday morning in the morning. Mother stopped at home to cook the meal. Sunday afternoon back to Sunday S
chool again. Then, we'd, you know, have a walk afterwards, not with the family, with the Sunday School sort of friends. And then Sunday tea, and then back to Chapel in the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 All of you in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, including Mother in the evening, 
you see, but not in the morning because Mother was cooking the meal. And that was the Sunday programme. And there'd be this walk afterwards. Then we would be together, like, but in the afternoon we'd have a walk with out Sunday School friends, you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Do you remember any activities of the Chapel, social or educational?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, there was the Band of Hope.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 You were telling me where the treat was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 That was, you know, quite a big event in the town. They used to have a long procession, we all
 used to march from the Co-Op store, round the town and then down to this field, you know, headed by the town band and, you know, we used to have tea and all the numerous sports, and there used to be such things as balloon ascents, you know, quite a field
 day.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Would you have races and competitions and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes, competitions where you could win, you know, sixpence or threepence, something like that, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And can you remember any other particular events in the town that you took part in, yourself and your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, no, not with the family, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did you go to concerts or music halls, or pantomimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No, that was out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Because of the money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, yes, and there was very little of that type of place in the town. Oh, no, never had any opportunity of getting to know any music.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And you weren't able to join the scouts for financial reasons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Oh, no, that's right, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 There was one thing I didn't mention in relation to my job at Courtaulds. We had a mechanics' institute in the town with a \'85
 quite a good library and Courtaulds used to subscribe to it and for that reason they used to get, oh, about half a dozen tickets, you see, which they used to, you know, give to the work people. And I had 
one of those, you know, early on, almost soon after I went there, like, and again that was a great help to me because, you see, there was plenty of books to browse amongst, and then, all the current magazines and the papers, and that. And there was the re
ading room where, you know, you could spend the evening, if you wanted in quiet, and that sort of thing, and I found that very handy. And I had a ticket, you know, up to the time, you know, when it closed down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 That must have made a big difference to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, it all helps, you see, 'cos, I mean, I hadn't the books at home and ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did you have any other educational outlets at that time? Did you go to any evening classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No. There were one or two, such as shorthand and things like that, but they were nearly all vocational.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 And they didn't appeal to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Well, I was \'85 it didn't appeal to me and another thing, you see, I was training as a \'85 for a mechanical job and as I say, shorthand 
\'85 it just didn't appeal to me. Anyway, it wouldn't've helped me at all. Then, of course, after the War I got involved in W.E.A., and \'85 see, I was only \'85
 I was 21 then. I got involved in the W.E.A. and in this adult school and, you know, I found it gave me what I wanted.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 When you went and read at the Mechanics' Institute, do you remember any books you read? Do you remember the titles of any of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
Well, I mean, there were all the recognized authors there then, I mean, Ryder Haggart's, and there were also, you know, the books of Jules Verne and H.G. Wells. They were all there, you know, as well as \'85 'course, there were Jane Austin, Thackary.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 You read the classics, too, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Yes. You know, they were all there which, of course, I knew nothing about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 Did you read mostly novels?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 
Yes, yes, mostly novels, yes. I don't remember sort of reading any of the very serious, you know, political works, like Pope and people like that, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14644286 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 You don't remember reading any poetry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8984427 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232 No. Later on, like, I did get interes
ted, sort of, in poetry, through this adult school, you know. Every year they used to have one or two subjects on, you know, \'85 well, not just contemporary poets, but \'85
 I'll show you one of the books. We had one of these every year, you see, a syllabus of sort of study. There was a certain religious bias to it, but you can see that \'85
 the sort of thing it was. And then, you see, they used to get someone to introduce the subject and then discuss it. And again, that brought me in touch with all sorts of things which I'd' ve never known about.
