You see, it was understandable it was born of her experience probably, but you see, after losing Father, and, sort of, we were young, well, she set about tackling her problem herself, you know, I mean, and \'85
.You know, this is all small, sort of, you know village talk, or town talk, but I can see the point in it, really, but you see, in this town as in most other towns and villages there are certain cha
ritable trusts and things, like, where the minister or some authority like that will dole out - or used to - a couple of cwt. of coal, or so many loaves for so many weeks, and that sort of thing. They had these trusts and they could do that, you see, and 
they were the sole arbiters of who should have it, or not, you see. Well, it was possible, you see, if you were a member of the Church, or if you pleaded your case sort of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2457556\charrsid6246232 skilfully}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4990402\charrsid6246232  and in the right place, you could get the assistance from these various charities, and that, you see. You see, my mother never did that sort of thing, it was alien to her nature, you see, but 
\'85 yet she resented the people who she knew had got it, you know, and as I say, you know, she hadn't much time for that sort of thing. As yo
u probably know, all over the country, like, there are people who donated, you know, say, so much money, or the interest to provide this for the poor, or that for the poor, and that sort of thing. Of course, it's all gone by the board now because it isn't
 necessary, but you see how it did lend itself. I well remember \'85
 I think what added point to Mother's attitude to it. Living, like, two houses from us there was a family, they were most prominent in the chapel that, you know, we used to attend, and the man
 was a deacon and all the family were members of the church, and that sort of thing, and although he was aline and working, you know, somehow or other he used to have free coal sent from this charity, you see. That's the sort of thing, you see. I mean, it
 was at the disposal of the minister and, sort of, those he liked had it and those he didn't, didn't get it. I don't mean it always worked out that way, but giving that \'85
 the sort of person administering it, it could do, you see. And as I say, you know, she hadn't no time for that, you know, she wouldn't \'85 it was alien in her nature to ask for anything. She set about, you know, solving her problem.
